The defendant Bryant Killebrew was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Vlack, DAR: Gross, Clerk: Rohan, ADA:   Michael Edward Nieskes   DF ATTY:  Jeffrey Lawrence Kemp   DF:  Bryant  Killebrew appeared from jail. Case called at 10:30 am. ADA Nieskes recites agreement. Atty. Kemp confirms. Off the record 10:31 am. On the record 10:32 am. Atty. Kemp requests restitution hearing be set. Off the record 10:34 am. On the record 10:56 am. Atty. Kemp files Plea Questionnaire. Court amends Count 1 to misdemeanor battery, per statute 940.199(1)(a). Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to amended Ct 1 in 15CF510. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. ADA Nieskes discusses pending extradition to MN, a hearing will be set if DEF remains in custody after 3/29 before Branch 4. Court does not resolve issue of restitution. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Court uses complaint to establish facts. ADA Nieskes request restitution hearing be set within 30 days before Court Commissioner. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1 in 15CF510. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:
 - 60 days sentence in St. Croix County Jail
- Credit for 144 days time served
- Court costs $243
- DNA surcharge $200
- Suspend collection of costs
Adjourned 11:06 am
Ad Testificandum. Filed by ADA Nieskes. km
